values:
MY life consists of working and shopping and going out.&nbsp;

I work wed to sat to earn $480 which of recently has gone to christmas shopping and going out. Pathetic I know. But i feel happy - well kind of.&nbsp;

I have officially ended things with jeff for now. I said we migh consider things in january but somehow I dont think it will work again. He tried to get me to gp back out with him but i said no due to something he told me and how we have been arpund each other recently. The hardest thing is moving on after your first love and I want to have another just not right away.

I have finished all of my christmas shopping. I just have to get my grandma her christmas cake, my uncles havianas&nbsp;and my second cousins husband something and Im sone. All in all Ive spent close to $500 which is a little overboard but my family and friends mean the word to me. Im not to sure if I should buy Jeff something but time will tell.

Last friday I seen Mondo Rock with my mum and uncle - twas fun and as such my mum and i ended up slightly tipsy and dancing in the olds disco at souths juniors. We also had a small party for my sister that sunday. Jai came over and we wrapped up some christmas presents together and chatted about things.

The past week all ive done is work and shop a little.&nbsp;

Friday night Jai and I joined, Daniel and Matt at Matts house where we had a night of fun and games. It was like old times. The boys and Jai getting drunk, (I was driving) tickling Matt, watching the meaning of life, singing, talking about sex, matt swaying, and laughing at daniels japanese friend Yooyah recite pick up lines. It was stupid enjoable fun.

Saturday night I went out to dinner with Mum, Dad, Alice, Julie and Eddy to italian. Was really good. We then bought Lebanese sweets ie baklava and all things almond and went to my grandparents. Uncle Jas and Dad drove me into the city for Anna Steels birthday bash at pavillion. Jai and I had a few drinks, chatted to people and left. It was getting boring and the music was crap.&nbsp;

Jai and I was waking to our fav venue ie the orient and on the way we stopped at the rocks cafe and had ricotta cheesecake which wasnt as good as the one from work and it cost $9.35&nbsp;

We eventually made it to the orient and within 10 minutes jaime was dancing with some guy and within another 5 she was pashing him ie being skank rat. I was getting bored so i waleked around talent spotting and eventually jai parted from her new friend and we talked. I was introduced to his cute and rather hot friend Richard who was a nurse.&nbsp; So I had someone to dance with and have fun with. We left the orient after lots of dancing and fun and started walking to get a cab still with the guys. It was fun until I grazed my elbow on a wall and Richard went into nurse mode trying to save me from pain. He was cute and he told me several times how beautiful and pretty I was. He wasnt sleazy at all and he wasnt exactly trying to sleep with me.&nbsp;

I kissed him and got butterflies ad he would just sit and&nbsp;stare at me in a content yet non-creepy fashion. His friend Dylan got into an empty wheelie bin and was being stupid. It was like hanging with the boys but we could kiss them and not feel horrible. We were next to this park at one point and under the light was a couple having sex in the middle of the city. Richards crazy friend Dylan went over and tried to hassle them with no effect reached.&nbsp;

They hailed us a cab and I was home by 4. I only had 7 drinks and was feeling a little sick at one point but I had an enjoyable yet pleasant night with a hot nurse that wasnt skanky or the slightest bit sleazy. He was cute and he wants to see me again but iM not going to rush into things thats for sure but he was a great kiss.&nbsp;

Tommorow Im planning on cleaning up all my old newspapers as ive wrapped all my christmas presents. Tuesday I might see if Erin wants to meet me in newtown for lunch and I might buy my christmas present to myself - the pink pearls i wanted. I got an extra $100&nbsp; to spend for christmas from my parents and i bought a black handbag and a scarf to tie around it. I have $50 left and my pearls are $125.&nbsp;

Ime xcited about christmas. Jai and I are going to have a bike gang for christmas and cruise between each others houses so we can get the best of all houses.&nbsp;

Anyway Im off to cover my new diary for 2007.

Love ya&nbsp;

Nat

IVe been thinking recently of a topic that will most probably be supported or completely hated but its something Ive been pondering and deserves a post as such.&nbsp;

Ive been thinking how no one ever sees anyone anymore and I miss everyone alot but no one ever makes the effort to see anyone or contact anyone. The only person I hear from on a regular basis is Jai and we are just about as busy as each other but we always make time for each other. Its not as if we all live far far away or have extentuatingly busy schedules. We are supposed to have friendships but it seems so many of us neglect them. Im not just talking about my male friends either some of my best friends I havent heard from in months which hurts but I dont think its my duty to be forever organising things.&nbsp;

So take it as you see fit this entry but some things are reality and in some respects this is not an attack on people but an insight into my thoughts and maybe a call for some correspondence and proactive behaviour.

I miss my friends :(

I have been busy in my own little way this week but not very busy.&nbsp;

Tuesday I went Christmas shopping with Jeff which was so much fun. I bought my parents, sisters and cousins present. I just have to buy my grandparents, jai, erin, my uncle and some others then Im done. So thats pretty cool.

Wednesday I cruised around home. Thursday I cruised about home some more then I went out to dinner with Jaime to Newtown for Thai. I was a little meh as I had some lower back pain but we chatted and entertained each other. We also had the best gelato from Gelatomassi on King St. I went home and the pain in my lower back was really bad so Friday I called in sick and didt go to work. I went to the doctor and I discovered I had a bladder infection so my kidneys were hurting.&nbsp;I have to go back on Monday for more results.&nbsp;

Friday afternoon I had my exam and considering I didnt do much study I think I went alright. I met up with Jeff afterwards and drove him home from Broadway.

Saturday I got up early to go to my sisters basketball game we then went shopping :P Mum bought me some gold thongs that have an ankle strap for an early christmas present and I bought some black pointy patent flats. I also got 6 new necklaces, a bracelet and some earrings for another early christmas present. Which means I will have less presents under the tree but more to wear now...

Saturday night I went out to dinner but my kidneys started to hurt again. Today I cruised around home and just had a relaxing day, reading, talking to my&nbsp;mum and eating :P I also went grocery shopping early in the morning - its apart of my chores when mum doesnt want to go.&nbsp;

Tommorow, Im going to vaccuum my grandparents house and do some studying. Other than an exam on Thursday and work on Wed, Fri and Sat Im pretty busy at the end of the week. Apparently Friday nite someones organising something. Saturday I think I have Sams dancing concert but I havent heard from her so I dont know. Anna was considering having something for her birthday on Saturday nite but Im not too sure. SO the end of the week is filled with maybes.&nbsp;

Ill just have to wait and see,&nbsp;
Till later,

Nat xo
